review.reviewBody:
@arbeck To be honest I haven't tried it that way, but I'm guessing it'd be pretty good. Definitely toast the cones beforehand. 

The Ideas in Food people tell me they've done a cone ice cream in a similar manner to their <a href="http://blog.ideasinfood.com/ideas_in_food/2011/12/shredded-wheat-ice-cream">shredded wheat</a>, which also follows a steep-and-strain process. 

Either way should taste nice&#8212;just about what kind of texture you want. I just like cookie-thickened ice creams so I went this way.
